verbose_text: Therefore, we evaluate this marginal effect at the fifth, tenth, twenty-fifth, fiftieth, seventy-fifth, ninetieth, and ninety-fifthth percentile levels of the male / female ratio in our sample, which correspond to 91.3, 94.0, 96.8, 99.1, 101.7, 105.7, and 108.4 males per 100 females, respectively.
